	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jul 22nd 9:45 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117530><span id=Guru>Calabar</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>214 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.75]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Though the run past the spiders always gives me the willies, I’d suggest going to Lake of Ill Omen.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can bind yourself in the Mill, port to another city to sell and then gate back.  That way you won’t have to make the run back to FV past those spiders unless you choose to do so.  You can fear kite the cats near the mill and then fear kite the tougher cats that roam towards the Sarnak Fort.  And should you wish to group, you can do that as well.  I believe you can hit at least level 30 in this area, should you with to do so.  <br><br>Or you cold check out Paludal Caverns on Luclin.  It’s very easy to get to. Catch the spires up to the Bazaar and then zone into Shadow Haven.  Both of these are safe zones, at least for good characters and I believe most evil ones as well.  You can zone into Paludal Caverns from Shadow Haven.  The experience is incredible there.  It’s quickly becoming the most popular zone for its level.  EQ Atlas lists its level as being 5 to 25, though I wouldn’t suggest going there before level 12.  The tunnel into the first cavern leads into a bandit camp.  These bandits will attack you no mater your level.  So you will need a group to fight there.  But there are other places you can fight, of course, that are not so intense.  But you might do best with at least one tank type as a partner no mater where you fight in the zone.  <br><br>Best of Luck,</p>&nbsp;<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 62nd Season<br><b>Jondor</b><br>Barbarian Beastlord, 54th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b> </td></td></tr>
